This works because `surchargesFor` is called inside an arrow body that's invoked later via `quote()`. By the time `itemSurchargeTotal` is invoked from `quote`, `surchargesFor` has been initialized. Good.

## Step 2: Calculate Current Mass (claim-related section only — the area we just touched)

Focused on lines 109-131 (claim logic):

```typescript
const DEDUCTIBLE = 100;
const HIGH_ENCHANTMENT_CLAIM_THRESHOLD = 8;
const HIGH_ENCHANTMENT_REIMBURSEMENT_RATE = 0.5;

const reimbursableAmount = (damage: Damage, item: Item | undefined): number => {
  if ((item?.enchantment ?? 0) >= HIGH_ENCHANTMENT_CLAIM_THRESHOLD) {
    return damage.amount * HIGH_ENCHANTMENT_REIMBURSEMENT_RATE;
  }
  return damage.amount;
};

const payoutForDamage = (damage: Damage, policy: Policy): number => {
  const item = policy.items.find((i) => i.type === damage.itemType);
  return reimbursableAmount(damage, item) - DEDUCTIBLE;
};

export const claim = (...): { payout: number; remainingCap: number } => {
  const payout = sum(incident.damages.map((damage) => payoutForDamage(damage, policy)));
  return { payout, remainingCap: policy.remainingCap - payout };
};
```

